      "name": "Product Info",
      "settings": {
        "width": "page",
        "header_type": "left",
        "heading": "<h2>The Right Way to Sharpen</h2>",
        "content": "<p>Pull-through sharpeners strip metal unevenly and damage your edge geometry. Electric sharpeners overheat the steel. A whetstone gives you full control over the angle, pressure, and finish — restoring a true, factory-sharp edge every time.</p>",
        "icon_block_state": true,
        "first_num": "3",
        "second_num": "3",
        "color_scheme": "scheme-5",
        "padding_top": 80,
        "padding_bottom": 80
      }
    },
    "product_info2_WS02": {
      "type": "product-info2",
      "name": "Product Info2",
      "settings": {
        "width": "page",
        "heading_title": "SHARPEN LIKE A PRO",
        "heading_content": "<h2>5-Minute Edge Restoration</h2>",
        "header_type": "left",
        "background_type": "none",
        "block_type": "text",
        "heading_footer": "",
        "image_video": "image",
        "color_scheme": "scheme-5",
        "footer_state": "visible",
        "footer_type": "first",
        "footer_left": "<h2>THE WHETSTONE ADVANTAGE</h2>",
        "footer_right": "<p>Unlike pull-throughs that gouge uneven grooves or electric grinders that overheat the steel, a whetstone lets you build a symmetrical, hair-splitting edge with nothing but water and patience. It’s the only method that actually improves your blade over time.</p>",
        "padding_top": 80,
        "padding_bottom": 80,
        "additional_footer": false,
        "additional_content1": "",
        "additional_content2": ""
      }
    },
    "product_info2_WS03": {
      "type": "product-info2",
      "name": "Product Info2",
      "settings": {
        "width": "page",
        "heading_title": "",
        "heading_content": "<h2>Designed for Xinzuo.<br/>Works with Everything.</h2>",
        "header_type": "center",
        "background_type": "none",
        "block_type": "text",
        "heading_footer": "",
        "image_video": "image",
        "color_scheme": "scheme-5",
        "footer_state": "visible",
        "footer_type": "third",
        "footer_left": "<p>We designed these stones specifically for the 15° edge angle used on Xinzuo knives — but they work beautifully on any kitchen knife. German, Japanese, or vintage — bring them all.</p>",
        "footer_right": "<p>Every whetstone set includes a sharpening angle guide so even first-timers get consistent results from day one.</p>",
        "padding_top": 80,
        "padding_bottom": 80,
        "additional_footer": false,
        "additional_content1": "",
